#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Pabbatavagga"
msgstr "1. Mountains"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 6. Kuṇḍaliyasutta → kuṇḍali (pts1)
msgctxt "sn46.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Kuṇḍaliyasutta"
msgstr "6. Kuṇḍaliya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.73"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: añjanavane → añcanavane (c1, c2)
msgctxt "sn46.6:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sākete viharati añjanavane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāketa in the deer part at the "
"Añjana Wood."

msgctxt "sn46.6:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kuṇḍaliyo paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the wanderer Kuṇḍaliya went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "sn46.6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho kuṇḍaliyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

#. VAR: ārāmanissayī → ārāmanisādī (bj) | ārāmaniyādi (s1-3) | ārāmanisādi (pts1)
msgctxt "sn46.6:1.4"
msgid "“ahamasmi, bho gotama, ārāmanissayī parisāvacaro."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, I like to hang around the monasteries and visit the "
"assemblies."

#. VAR: ayamācāro → ayamāhāro (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "sn46.6:1.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bho gotama, pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāsassa ayamācāro hoti—"
msgstr "When I’ve finished breakfast, it’s my habit to"

msgctxt "sn46.6:1.6"
msgid "ārāmena ārāmaṃ uyyānena uyyānaṃ anucaṅkamāmi anuvicarāmi."
msgstr "wander from monastery to monastery, from park to park."

msgctxt "sn46.6:1.7"
msgid ""
"So tattha passāmi eke samaṇabrāhmaṇe itivādappamokkhānisaṃsañceva kathaṃ "
"kathente upārambhānisaṃsañca:"
msgstr ""
"There I see some ascetics and brahmins speaking for the sake of winning "
"debates and finding fault."

# extra quotes here are unnecessary.
msgctxt "sn46.6:1.8"
msgid "‘bhavaṃ pana gotamo kimānisaṃso viharatī’”ti?"
msgstr "But what benefit does Master Gotama live for?”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:1.9"
msgid "“Vijjāvimuttiphalānisaṃso kho, kuṇḍaliya, tathāgato viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The benefit the Realized One lives for, Kuṇḍaliya, is the fruit of "
"knowledge and freedom.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.74"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Katame pana, bho gotama, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ "
"paripūrentī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what things must be developed and cultivated in order to fulfill "
"knowledge and freedom?”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Satta kho, kuṇḍaliya, bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ "
"paripūrentī”ti."
msgstr "“The seven awakening factors.”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Katame pana, bho gotama, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge "
"paripūrentī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what things must be developed and cultivated in order to fulfill the "
"seven awakening factors?”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Cattāro kho, kuṇḍaliya, satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge "
"paripūrentī”ti."
msgstr "“The four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.5"
msgid ""
"“Katame pana, bho gotama, dhammā bhāvitā, bahulīkatā cattāro satipaṭṭhāne "
"paripūrentī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what things must be developed and cultivated in order to fulfill the "
"four kinds of mindfulness meditation?”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Tīṇi kho, kuṇḍaliya, sucaritāni bhāvitāni bahulīkatāni cattāro satipaṭṭhāne "
"paripūrentī”ti."
msgstr "“The three kinds of good conduct.”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.7"
msgid ""
"“Katame pana, bho gotama, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā tīṇi sucaritāni "
"paripūrentī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what things must be developed and cultivated in order to fulfill the "
"three kinds of good conduct?”"

msgctxt "sn46.6:2.8"
msgid ""
"“Indriyasaṃvaro kho, kuṇḍaliya, bhāvito bahulīkato tīṇi sucaritāni "
"paripūretīti."
msgstr "“Sense restraint."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, kuṇḍaliya, indriyasaṃvaro kathaṃ bahulīkato tīṇi "
"sucaritāni paripūretīti?"
msgstr ""
"And Kuṇḍaliya, how is sense restraint developed and cultivated so as to "
"fulfill the three kinds of good conduct?"

msgctxt "sn46.6:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, kuṇḍaliya, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā manāpaṃ nābhijjhati "
"nābhihaṃsati, na rāgaṃ janeti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant sees an agreeable sight with their eye. They don’t desire it or "
"enjoy it, and they don’t give rise to greed."

msgctxt "sn46.6:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa ṭhito ca kāyo hoti, ṭhitaṃ cittaṃ ajjhattaṃ susaṇṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ."
msgstr "Their mind and body are steady internally, well settled and well freed."

msgctxt "sn46.6:3.4"
msgid ""
"Cakkhunā kho paneva rūpaṃ disvā amanāpaṃ na maṅku hoti appatiṭṭhitacitto "
"adīnamānaso abyāpannacetaso."
msgstr ""
"But if they see a disagreeable sight they’re not dismayed; their mind isn’t "
"hardened, dejected, or full of ill will."

msgctxt "sn46.6:3.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa ṭhito ca kāyo hoti ṭhitaṃ cittaṃ ajjhattaṃ susaṇṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ."
msgstr "Their mind and body are steady internally, well settled and well freed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, kuṇḍaliya, bhikkhu sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant hears an agreeable sound with the ear …"

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.2"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "smells an agreeable odor with the nose …"

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.3"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "tastes an agreeable flavor with the tongue …"

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.4"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …"
msgstr "feels an agreeable touch with the body …"

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.5"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya manāpaṃ nābhijjhati nābhihaṃsati, na rāgaṃ janeti."
msgstr ""
"knows an agreeable thought with their mind. They don’t desire it or enjoy "
"it, and they don’t give rise to greed."

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.6"
msgid ""
"Tassa ṭhito ca kāyo hoti, ṭhitaṃ cittaṃ ajjhattaṃ susaṇṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ."
msgstr "Their mind and body are steady internally, well settled and well freed."

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.7"
msgid ""
"Manasā kho paneva dhammaṃ viññāya amanāpaṃ na maṅku hoti appatiṭṭhitacitto "
"adīnamānaso abyāpannacetaso."
msgstr ""
"But if they know a disagreeable thought they’re not dismayed; their mind isn’"
"t hardened, dejected, or full of ill will."

msgctxt "sn46.6:4.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa ṭhito ca kāyo hoti, ṭhitaṃ cittaṃ ajjhattaṃ susaṇṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ."
msgstr "Their mind and body are steady internally, well settled and well freed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.75"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:5.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kuṇḍaliya, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā manāpāmanāpesu rūpesu "
"ṭhito ca kāyo hoti, ṭhitaṃ cittaṃ ajjhattaṃ susaṇṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant’s mind and body are steady internally, they’re well settled "
"and well freed when it comes to both agreeable and disagreeable sights,"

msgctxt "sn46.6:5.2"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "sounds,"

msgctxt "sn46.6:5.3"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "smells,"

msgctxt "sn46.6:5.4"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "tastes,"

msgctxt "sn46.6:5.5"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …"
msgstr "touches,"

msgctxt "sn46.6:5.6"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya manāpāmanāpesu dhammesu ṭhito ca kāyo hoti, ṭhitaṃ "
"cittaṃ ajjhattaṃ susaṇṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ."
msgstr "and thoughts."

msgctxt "sn46.6:5.7"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvito kho, kuṇḍaliya, indriyasaṃvaro evaṃ bahulīkato tīṇi sucaritāni "
"paripūreti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how sense restraint is developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the "
"three kinds of good conduct."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:6.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvitāni ca, kuṇḍaliya, tīṇi sucaritāni kathaṃ bahulīkatāni cattāro "
"satipaṭṭhāne paripūrenti?"
msgstr ""
"And how are the three kinds of good conduct developed and cultivated so as "
"to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation?"

msgctxt "sn46.6:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, kuṇḍaliya, bhikkhu kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, "
"vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya "
"manosucaritaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant gives up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and "
"develops good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "sn46.6:6.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitāni kho, kuṇḍaliya, tīṇi sucaritāni evaṃ bahulīkatāni cattāro "
"satipaṭṭhāne paripūrenti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how the three kinds of good conduct are developed and cultivated so "
"as to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:7.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, kuṇḍaliya, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā kathaṃ bahulīkatā satta "
"bojjhaṅge paripūrenti?"
msgstr ""
"And how are the four kinds of mindfulness meditation developed and "
"cultivated so as to fulfill the seven awakening factors?"

msgctxt "sn46.6:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, kuṇḍaliya, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and "
"mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn46.6:7.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn46.6:7.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn46.6:7.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn46.6:7.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, kuṇḍaliya, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā evaṃ bahulīkatā satta "
"bojjhaṅge paripūrenti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how the four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and "
"cultivated so as to fulfill the seven awakening factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:8.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, kuṇḍaliya, satta bojjhaṅgā kathaṃ bahulīkatā "
"vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrenti?"
msgstr ""
"And how are the seven awakening factors developed and cultivated so as to "
"fulfill knowledge and freedom?"

msgctxt "sn46.6:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, kuṇḍaliya, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ "
"virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ "
"bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of "
"principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which "
"rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.6:8.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, kuṇḍaliya, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ "
"paripūrentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to "
"fulfill knowledge and freedom.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.6:9.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kuṇḍaliyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderer Kuṇḍaliya said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn46.6:9.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "sn46.6:9.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evameva bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "sn46.6:9.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn46.6:9.5"
msgid ""
"Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.6:9.6"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
